div.p:
Ibn Habal was born in Baghdad by the Portico Gate in Thamil Lane on the twenty-third of Dhū l-Qaʿdah in the year 515 [2 February 1122]. He grew up in Baghdad and studied belles-lettres (
adab
) and medicine and also learned traditions there from Abū l-Qāsim Ismāʿīl ibn Aḥmad ibn al-Samarqandī. Then he went to Mosul where he lived until the time of his death.

